---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const updated = 'March 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service — T1V App" description="Terms of Service for the T1V App by Turn1Visuals.">

  <section class="tos-section">
    <div class="container tos-inner">

      <header class="tos-header">
        <p class="section-label">T1V App</p>
        <h1 class="tos-title">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="tos-meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
      </header>

      <div class="prose">

        <p>
          These Terms of Service govern your use of the T1V App ("the App"), a personal desktop application
          developed by Turn1Visuals for managing and publishing Formula 1 content across social media platforms
          including TikTok, YouTube, and Twitch.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By using the T1V App, you agree to these Terms of Service. If you do not agree, do not use the App.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Description of the App</h2>
        <p>
          The T1V App is a personal-use Electron desktop application that provides the following functionality:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Uploading video content to TikTok, YouTube, and other platforms</li>
          <li>Managing live stream sessions via OBS integration</li>
          <li>Sending messages to live chat on connected platforms</li>
          <li>Organizing workflow tools and launcher shortcuts</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          The App is intended solely for personal use by the owner of the Turn1Visuals account and is not
          distributed to the public.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Use of Third-Party APIs</h2>
        <p>
          The App integrates with third-party platforms including TikTok, YouTube, and Twitch via their
          respective official APIs. Use of these integrations is subject to each platform's own Terms of Service:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://www.tiktok.com/legal/page/global/terms-of-service/en" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TikTok Terms of Service</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/t/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">YouTube Terms of Service</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.twitch.tv/p/legal/terms-of-service/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Twitch Terms of Service</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Data and Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          The App does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data to external servers operated by
          Turn1Visuals. All configuration data (API credentials, OAuth tokens, settings) is stored locally
          on the user's device in the application data directory.
        </p>
        <p>
          Authentication with third-party platforms uses OAuth 2.0. Access tokens are stored locally and
          used only to communicate directly with the respective platform's API on behalf of the user.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Content Responsibility</h2>
        <p>
          The user is solely responsible for all content uploaded or streamed through the App. Turn1Visuals
          does not review, moderate, or take responsibility for any content published via the App.
          All content must comply with the terms and community guidelines of the target platforms.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          The T1V App and its source code are the property of Turn1Visuals. Unauthorized copying,
          distribution, or modification of the App is prohibited.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          The App is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. Turn1Visuals makes no guarantees
          regarding uptime, accuracy, or fitness for any particular purpose. Use of the App is at your
          own risk.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, Turn1Visuals shall not be liable for any indirect,
          incidental, or consequential damages arising from the use of the App or its integrations
          with third-party platforms.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms may be updated from time to time. Continued use of the App after changes are posted
          constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about these Terms, contact Turn1Visuals at
          <a href="mailto:info@turn1visuals.com">info@turn1visuals.com</a>.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .tos-section {
    padding-block: var(--space-section);
  }

  .tos-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .tos-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .tos-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-block: 0.75rem 0.5rem;
  }

  .tos-meta {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  /* ── Prose ── */
  .prose {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .prose h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
    padding-top: 0;
    border-top: none;
  }

  .prose ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .prose ul li {
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .prose ul li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
</style>
